.SH NAME
Net::Nostr::Client \- WebSocket client for Nostr relays
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 3
\&    use Net::Nostr::Client;
\&    use Net::Nostr::Key;
\&    use Net::Nostr::Filter;
\&
\&    my $key    = Net::Nostr::Key\->new;
\&    my $client = Net::Nostr::Client\->new;
\&
\&    # Register callbacks before connecting
\&    $client\->on(event => sub {
\&        my ($sub_id, $event) = @_;
\&        say "Got event: " . $event\->content;
\&    });
\&
\&    $client\->on(ok => sub {
\&        my ($event_id, $accepted, $message) = @_;
\&        say $accepted ? "Accepted" : "Rejected: $message";
\&    });
\&
\&    $client\->on(eose => sub {
\&        my ($sub_id) = @_;
\&        say "End of stored events for $sub_id";
\&    });
\&
\&    # Connect (blocks until connected, croaks on failure)
\&    $client\->connect("wss://relay.example.com");
\&
\&    # Create and publish an event
\&    my $event = $key\->create_event(kind => 1, content => \*(Aqhello\*(Aq, tags => []);
\&    $client\->publish($event);
\&
\&    # Subscribe with one or more filters
\&    my $filter = Net::Nostr::Filter\->new(kinds => [1], limit => 20);
\&    $client\->subscribe(\*(Aqmy\-feed\*(Aq, $filter);
\&
\&    # Close a subscription
\&    $client\->close(\*(Aqmy\-feed\*(Aq);
\&
\&    # Disconnect
\&    $client\->disconnect;
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
A WebSocket client for connecting to Nostr relays. Provides a callback\-based
interface for publishing events, managing subscriptions, receiving relay
messages, counting events (NIP\-45), and negentropy set reconciliation
(NIP\-77). Supports NIP\-42 authentication.
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.IX Header "CONSTRUCTOR"
.SS new
.IX Subsection "new"
.Vb 1
\&    my $client = Net::Nostr::Client\->new;
.Ve
.PP
Creates a new client instance. No connection is established until
\&\f(CW\*(C`connect\*(C'\fR is called. Croaks on unknown arguments.
.SH METHODS
.IX Header "METHODS"
.SS connect
.IX Subsection "connect"
.Vb 1
\&    $client\->connect($url);
\&
\&    # Non\-blocking with callback:
\&    $client\->connect($url, sub { ... });
.Ve
.PP
Connects to the relay at the given WebSocket URL. Blocks until the
connection is established and returns \f(CW$self\fR for chaining. Croaks
if the connection fails, \f(CW$url\fR is not provided, or the callback
is not a CODE ref.
.PP
If a callback is provided, connects asynchronously and returns
immediately without blocking. The callback receives a single argument:
\&\f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR on success, or an error string on failure.
.PP
.Vb 8
\&    $client\->connect($url, sub {
\&        my ($err) = @_;
\&        if ($err) {
\&            warn "Connection failed: $err";
\&            return;
\&        }
\&        # connected successfully
\&    });
.Ve
.SS is_connected
.IX Subsection "is_connected"
.Vb 1
\&    if ($client\->is_connected) { ... }
.Ve
.PP
Returns true if the client has an active WebSocket connection.
.SS disconnect
.IX Subsection "disconnect"
.Vb 1
\&    $client\->disconnect;
.Ve
.PP
Closes the WebSocket connection. \f(CW\*(C`is_connected\*(C'\fR will return false
afterwards. The connection is also automatically cleared if the
relay drops the connection.
.SS publish
.IX Subsection "publish"
.Vb 1
\&    $client\->publish($event);
.Ve
.PP
Sends an EVENT message to the relay. The relay will respond with an OK
message (received via the \f(CW\*(C`ok\*(C'\fR callback). Croaks if not connected.
.PP
.Vb 3
\&    my $key   = Net::Nostr::Key\->new;
\&    my $event = $key\->create_event(kind => 1, content => \*(Aqhello\*(Aq, tags => []);
\&    $client\->publish($event);
.Ve
.SS subscribe
.IX Subsection "subscribe"
.Vb 1
\&    $client\->subscribe(\*(Aqsub\-id\*(Aq, $filter1, $filter2);
.Ve
.PP
Sends a REQ message to the relay with the given subscription ID and
filters. The relay will send matching stored events (via \f(CW\*(C`event\*(C'\fR
callback), then an EOSE message (via \f(CW\*(C`eose\*(C'\fR callback), then live
events as they arrive. Croaks if not connected.
.SS count
.IX Subsection "count"
.Vb 1
\&    $client\->count(\*(Aqquery\-id\*(Aq, $filter1, $filter2);
.Ve
.PP
Sends a COUNT message (NIP\-45) to the relay with the given query ID and
filters. The relay will respond with a count (received via the \f(CW\*(C`count\*(C'\fR
callback). Unlike \f(CW\*(C`subscribe\*(C'\fR, COUNT is one\-shot and does not create a
live subscription. Croaks if not connected.
.PP
.Vb 7
\&    $client\->on(count => sub {
\&        my ($query_id, $count, $approximate) = @_;
\&        say "Got $count events" . ($approximate ? \*(Aq (approximate)\*(Aq : \*(Aq\*(Aq);
\&    });
\&    $client\->count(\*(Aqfollowers\*(Aq, Net::Nostr::Filter\->new(
\&        kinds => [3], \*(Aq#p\*(Aq => [$pubkey],
\&    ));
.Ve
.SS close
.IX Subsection "close"
.Vb 1
\&    $client\->close(\*(Aqsub\-id\*(Aq);
.Ve
.PP
Sends a CLOSE message to stop receiving events for the given
subscription ID. Croaks if not connected.
.SS neg_open
.IX Subsection "neg_open"
.Vb 1
\&    $client\->neg_open($sub_id, $filter, $initial_msg);
.Ve
.PP
Sends a NEG\-OPEN message (NIP\-77) to initiate negentropy set reconciliation.
\&\f(CW$filter\fR is a Net::Nostr::Filter object, and \f(CW$initial_msg\fR is the
hex\-encoded initial message from "initiate" in Net::Nostr::Negentropy.
The relay will respond with a \f(CW\*(C`neg_msg\*(C'\fR callback. Croaks if not connected.
.PP
Subscription IDs are in a separate namespace from \f(CW\*(C`subscribe\*(C'\fR. If a
NEG\-OPEN is issued for a currently open subscription ID, the relay
closes the existing session first.
.PP
.Vb 1
\&    use Net::Nostr::Negentropy;
\&
\&    my $ne = Net::Nostr::Negentropy\->new;
\&    # add local events via $ne\->add_item(...)
\&    $ne\->seal;
\&    $client\->neg_open(\*(Aqsync1\*(Aq, $filter, $ne\->initiate);
.Ve
.SS neg_msg
.IX Subsection "neg_msg"
.Vb 1
\&    $client\->neg_msg($sub_id, $msg);
.Ve
.PP
Sends a NEG\-MSG message (NIP\-77) to continue a negentropy reconciliation
round. \f(CW$msg\fR is the hex\-encoded message from "reconcile" in Net::Nostr::Negentropy.
Croaks if not connected.
.SS neg_close
.IX Subsection "neg_close"
.Vb 1
\&    $client\->neg_close($sub_id);
.Ve
.PP
Sends a NEG\-CLOSE message (NIP\-77) to terminate a negentropy session and
release relay resources. Croaks if not connected.
.SS authenticate
.IX Subsection "authenticate"
.Vb 1
\&    $client\->authenticate($key, $relay_url);
.Ve
.PP
Sends a NIP\-42 AUTH event to the relay. The \f(CW$key\fR is a
Net::Nostr::Key object used to sign the authentication event,
and \f(CW$relay_url\fR is the relay\*(Aqs URL for the \f(CW\*(C`relay\*(C'\fR tag.
.PP
The client must have received an AUTH challenge from the relay first
(stored in \f(CW\*(C`challenge\*(C'\fR). Croaks if not connected, if \f(CW$key\fR or
\&\f(CW$relay_url\fR is missing, or if no challenge has been received.
.PP
.Vb 4
\&    $client\->on(auth => sub {
\&        my ($challenge) = @_;
\&        $client\->authenticate($key, \*(Aqwss://relay.example.com/\*(Aq);
\&    });
.Ve
.SS challenge
.IX Subsection "challenge"
.Vb 1
\&    my $challenge = $client\->challenge;
.Ve
.PP
Returns the most recent AUTH challenge string received from the relay,
or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR if no challenge has been received.
.SS on
.IX Subsection "on"
.Vb 1
\&    $client\->on($event_type => sub { ... });
.Ve
.PP
Registers a callback for relay messages. The callback must be a CODE
ref; croaks otherwise. Only one callback may be registered per event
type \-\- calling \f(CW\*(C`on\*(C'\fR again for the same type replaces the previous
callback. Supported event types:
.ie n .IP """event"" \- ""sub { my ($subscription_id, $event) = @_; }""" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWevent\fR \- \f(CWsub { my ($subscription_id, $event) = @_; }\fR" 4
.IX Item "event - sub { my ($subscription_id, $event) = @_; }"
Called for each EVENT message from the relay (both stored and live).
.ie n .IP """ok"" \- ""sub { my ($event_id, $accepted, $message) = @_; }""" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWok\fR \- \f(CWsub { my ($event_id, $accepted, $message) = @_; }\fR" 4
.IX Item "ok - sub { my ($event_id, $accepted, $message) = @_; }"
Called when the relay responds to a published event.
.ie n .IP """eose"" \- ""sub { my ($subscription_id) = @_; }""" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWeose\fR \- \f(CWsub { my ($subscription_id) = @_; }\fR" 4
.IX Item "eose - sub { my ($subscription_id) = @_; }"
Called when the relay finishes sending stored events for a subscription.
.ie n .IP """notice"" \- ""sub { my ($message) = @_; }""" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWnotice\fR \- \f(CWsub { my ($message) = @_; }\fR" 4
.IX Item "notice - sub { my ($message) = @_; }"
Called when the relay sends a human\-readable NOTICE.
.ie n .IP """count"" \- ""sub { my ($query_id, $count, $approximate) = @_; }""" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWcount\fR \- \f(CWsub { my ($query_id, $count, $approximate) = @_; }\fR" 4
.IX Item "count - sub { my ($query_id, $count, $approximate) = @_; }"
Called when the relay responds to a COUNT request (NIP\-45). \f(CW$count\fR is
the number of matching events, \f(CW$approximate\fR is true if the count is
probabilistic. HyperLogLog (\f(CW\*(C`hll\*(C'\fR) values are not currently parsed.
.ie n .IP """closed"" \- ""sub { my ($subscription_id, $message) = @_; }""" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWclosed\fR \- \f(CWsub { my ($subscription_id, $message) = @_; }\fR" 4
.IX Item "closed - sub { my ($subscription_id, $message) = @_; }"
Called when the relay closes a subscription.
.ie n .IP """auth"" \- ""sub { my ($challenge) = @_; }""" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWauth\fR \- \f(CWsub { my ($challenge) = @_; }\fR" 4
.IX Item "auth - sub { my ($challenge) = @_; }"
Called when the relay sends an AUTH challenge (NIP\-42). The client
should respond by calling \f(CW\*(C`authenticate\*(C'\fR.
.ie n .IP """neg_msg"" \- ""sub { my ($subscription_id, $msg) = @_; }""" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWneg_msg\fR \- \f(CWsub { my ($subscription_id, $msg) = @_; }\fR" 4
.IX Item "neg_msg - sub { my ($subscription_id, $msg) = @_; }"
Called when the relay sends a NEG\-MSG response (NIP\-77). \f(CW$msg\fR is the
hex\-encoded negentropy message to pass to "reconcile" in Net::Nostr::Negentropy.
.ie n .IP """neg_err"" \- ""sub { my ($subscription_id, $message) = @_; }""" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWneg_err\fR \- \f(CWsub { my ($subscription_id, $message) = @_; }\fR" 4
.IX Item "neg_err - sub { my ($subscription_id, $message) = @_; }"
Called when the relay sends a NEG\-ERR (NIP\-77). The negentropy session
is considered closed after this.
